Lagos State Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu has urged Nigerians to give All Progressives Congress (APC) National Leader Asiwaju Bola Tinubu a chance to be president come 2023. According to Sanwo-Olu, Tinubu knows the issues plaguing the country, hence has the solutions. He urged lawmakers in Lagos State to work towards ensuring that Tinubu becomes Nigeria’s next president. Fire Claims 1, 17 Others Injured In Borno IDP Camp Group Warns Detractors From Distracting Akinwumi, Lokoja Varsity… He said, “Tinubu knows the issues plaguing our nation like the back of his hands and he has the magic wand to fix it. “So, because of our Apex Leader, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, it is time for us to take Lagos to Nigeria’s agenda. “That is why I am calling on all of us to ensure that we do everything we can do politically and otherwise, to ensure that we can help to activate and actualise the next president of Nigeria, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu.”